WEBVTT

00:02.086 --> 00:03.421
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on:</i>

00:03.586 --> 00:05.756
DAMON: Where the hell are we?
BONNIE: 1994.

00:05.923 --> 00:08.092
KAI: To get home,
harness the power of the Ascendant.

00:08.259 --> 00:10.886
ELENA: What about Bonnie?
DAMON: She sacrificed herself for me.

00:11.053 --> 00:12.930
- She's all alone.
- We miss you, Bonnie.

00:13.097 --> 00:14.265
BONNIE:
I miss you guys.

00:14.432 --> 00:17.101
- Sorry I compelled away the memories.
- We'll make new ones.

00:17.518 --> 00:19.061
FORBES:
Promise me something.

00:19.228 --> 00:23.107
When I'm gone, Caroline is gonna need you
to help her move on with her life.

00:23.274 --> 00:25.609
- Promise me that you will do that, Stefan.
- I promise.

00:25.776 --> 00:28.696
In our coven's tradition
the twins merge their strength.

00:28.863 --> 00:29.947
The weaker one dies.

00:30.114 --> 00:33.367
I know I'm stronger than Liv
so that means I will win if we merge.

00:33.534 --> 00:36.078
MR. PARKER:
One twin will absorb traits from the other.

00:36.245 --> 00:38.622
Both of your souls
will unite into a new being.

00:39.331 --> 00:41.208
Luke, don't!

00:41.375 --> 00:43.252
[CHANTING IN LATIN]

00:44.045 --> 00:45.421
Luke is gone.

00:45.588 --> 00:47.465
He merged with Kai. Kai won.

00:47.798 --> 00:49.133
KAI:
You win some, you lose some.

00:49.300 --> 00:51.010
Except for me, I always win.

00:58.392 --> 01:00.227
[ICE CUBE'S "CHECK YO SELF"
PLAYING ON STEREO]

01:00.394 --> 01:02.772
MAN [RAPPING]: <i>I'm bad for your health
I come real stealth</i>

01:02.938 --> 01:05.316
<i>Droppin' bombs on ya moms
Break car alarms</i>

01:05.483 --> 01:07.818
<i>Doin' foul crime
I'm that brotha wit'cha Alpine</i>

01:07.985 --> 01:10.488
<i>Sold it for a six-o
Always let tricks know</i>

01:10.654 --> 01:12.573
<i>And friends know We got the indo</i>

01:12.740 --> 01:15.451
<i>No, I'm not a sucker
Sittin' in a House of Pain</i>

01:15.618 --> 01:17.369
<i>And, no, I'm not the butler
I'll cut ya</i>

01:17.536 --> 01:19.705
<i>Headbutt ya
You say you can't touch this</i>

01:19.872 --> 01:22.124
<i>And I wouldn't touch ya
In fact I'll buck ya</i>

01:22.291 --> 01:24.251
<i>Here to let you know boy, oh, boy</i>

01:24.418 --> 01:26.921
Happy birthday, Bonnie.

01:27.088 --> 01:29.173
<i>This ain't no kind of motion picture</i>

01:29.340 --> 01:31.467
<i>A guy or chick-a
I'll get wit'cha</i>

01:31.634 --> 01:34.220
<i>And hit ya
Takin' that yack to the neck</i>

01:34.386 --> 01:36.514
<i>So you better run a check</i>

01:44.855 --> 01:46.232
[GRUNTING]

01:50.611 --> 01:52.238
ELENA:
Hey.

01:56.784 --> 01:59.036
You wanna give me a hand, please.

01:59.203 --> 02:00.538
A little busy here.

02:00.704 --> 02:03.707
Okay, fine, then you are
on decoration duty.

02:03.874 --> 02:05.126
It's Bonnie's birthday.

02:05.584 --> 02:07.128
I know what today is.

02:07.294 --> 02:09.045
You know how she'd want us to spend it.

02:09.213 --> 02:12.341
She would have wanted us to celebrate
by cooking her favorite food...

02:12.508 --> 02:14.051
...watching her favorite movies.

02:14.218 --> 02:17.388
So we're throwing a birthday party
where the guest of honor never shows up.

02:17.555 --> 02:19.849
That's not depressing.

02:20.015 --> 02:22.059
Or we could celebrate you going
to art school.

02:22.935 --> 02:26.313
Oh, wait, we can't because I found
your application in the garbage.

02:27.148 --> 02:29.650
Why didn't you tell me
about going to art school?

02:30.651 --> 02:33.529
I'm not. The only class I'm passing
is study hall.

02:33.696 --> 02:34.989
They'll never let me in.

02:35.156 --> 02:37.616
Jer, I've seen your portfolio.

02:38.200 --> 02:40.035
- You're good.
- It doesn't matter.

02:40.202 --> 02:42.663
I'm not leaving without knowing
if Bonnie's okay or not.

02:44.248 --> 02:46.584
Mom, I'm not calling to check up on you.

02:46.750 --> 02:49.253
I'm just about to start
making Bonnie's birthday cake.

02:49.420 --> 02:52.715
I wanna make sure your recipe called
for three eggs instead of four, right?

02:52.882 --> 02:55.759
All right, I'm just a phone call away,
in case you need any...

02:55.926 --> 02:57.386
Bye.

02:58.429 --> 03:00.431
[GASPS, THEN SIGHS]

03:02.850 --> 03:06.103
Is it just me or do her eyes
follow you around the room?

03:06.520 --> 03:07.980
STEFAN:
Hmm.

03:09.023 --> 03:10.816
It's definitely you.

03:11.775 --> 03:14.278
I haven't seen Miss Cuddles in 12 years.

03:14.445 --> 03:17.239
Well, that's the bear
Bonnie sent back from 1994.

03:17.406 --> 03:19.909
- I guess she lost the original.
- She didn't lose her.

03:20.701 --> 03:22.077
I took her.

03:23.537 --> 03:26.624
You know, when Bonnie and I were little,
we got in this huge fight.

03:26.790 --> 03:27.917
So to get back at her...

03:28.083 --> 03:30.377
...I bearnapped Miss Cuddles.

03:30.544 --> 03:33.756
I didn't want my mom to come home
and find out, so then I buried her...

03:33.923 --> 03:35.007
...in the woods.

03:35.174 --> 03:38.135
I even left some M&M's
to mark the spot where I left her...

03:38.302 --> 03:40.554
...but something
must have eaten them.

03:40.721 --> 03:43.599
Well, I'm pretty sure
that Bonnie is over it by now.

03:44.767 --> 03:45.976
Miss Cuddles isn't.

03:47.061 --> 03:49.813
She's out there, all alone...

03:50.314 --> 03:52.066
...like Bonnie.

03:52.233 --> 03:54.777
You know what? I'm gonna go find her.

03:55.486 --> 03:57.655
- You're gonna what?
- Yeah, it's Bonnie's birthday.

03:57.821 --> 04:00.741
Wait, wait, hold on.
You've been going through a lot lately.

04:00.908 --> 04:04.954
You think that maybe you're just a little
confused about what you're upset about?

04:05.746 --> 04:07.623
Yes, probably.

04:07.790 --> 04:10.918
My mom's dying and my best friend
is stuck in an alternate universe...

04:11.085 --> 04:12.920
...and her bear is in a hole in the woods.

04:13.379 --> 04:16.339
There's only one of those things
that I can do anything about.

04:16.673 --> 04:18.175
Right.

04:20.219 --> 04:22.137
Happy birthday, Bon-bon.

04:24.348 --> 04:25.808
DAMON:
Hi.

04:26.684 --> 04:29.353
Ooh. Think we could sneak one
before the party?

04:29.520 --> 04:33.274
- I think Caroline might fry us in the sun.
- It's worth the risk.

04:35.734 --> 04:36.944
Mmm.

04:37.111 --> 04:38.570
Come here.

04:44.618 --> 04:47.246
You know, we never talked about...

04:47.746 --> 04:51.208
- ...the fact that you kissed me.
- And you kissed me back.

04:51.375 --> 04:52.543
- Yeah.
- I know.

04:52.710 --> 04:55.671
That's the whole point of kissing,
you don't have to talk about it.

04:55.838 --> 04:57.798
Right, well, I just wanted you to know...

04:58.757 --> 05:01.093
- ...that I'm good with that.
- Yeah?

05:01.260 --> 05:03.304
Yeah, we're good.

05:03.470 --> 05:04.555
Really good.

05:04.722 --> 05:05.889
[ELENA CHUCKLES]

05:06.056 --> 05:07.141
Is this the talk?

05:07.850 --> 05:10.102
- Pretty much.
- Perfect.

05:11.061 --> 05:12.104
[DOOR OPENS]

05:12.271 --> 05:13.981
KAI:
Hello.

05:14.148 --> 05:15.232
No.

05:15.399 --> 05:18.569
- That's impossible, because why
would he...? DAMON: He didn't.

05:18.736 --> 05:21.280
He's all merged, he's packed
and he's on his way to Portland.

05:21.447 --> 05:24.325
Whew. I forgot how massive
this house was.

05:24.491 --> 05:25.743
Yum, cupcakes.

05:25.909 --> 05:27.745
Sorry, am I interrupting something?

05:27.911 --> 05:30.164
- What are you doing here?
- Funniest thing.

05:31.248 --> 05:32.833
I need your help.

05:33.000 --> 05:35.002
Why would we give a letter to Jo?

05:35.169 --> 05:37.087
I can't find her using a locator spell.

05:37.254 --> 05:39.006
And, you know, good on her...

05:39.173 --> 05:42.760
...under normal circumstances, I'd be
jazzed to gouge out her belly button.

05:42.926 --> 05:46.764
- Why would we help you, Kai?
- In case you haven't figured out by now...

05:46.930 --> 05:48.140
...I'm a sociopath.

05:48.599 --> 05:51.060
I know, shocker.
I like being a sociopath, you know.

05:51.226 --> 05:53.687
I'm not burned by things
like guilt or love.

05:54.104 --> 05:57.274
So then, this merge happened
with my brother Luke, and I won.

05:57.441 --> 05:59.777
Great, because I absorbed his ability
to do magic...

05:59.943 --> 06:03.238
...but now I can't stop thinking
about how Luke died.

06:04.073 --> 06:05.824
How Liv's life is ruined.

06:06.325 --> 06:08.619
For some horrible reason, I can't shake...

06:09.161 --> 06:11.288
...how badly I feel about it.

06:11.455 --> 06:14.958
- You feel bad?
- Yeah. So when I absorbed Luke's magic...

06:15.125 --> 06:20.089
...I must have gotten some of his qualities
or something, like empathy.

06:20.255 --> 06:22.800
So I Googled
how to process emotional pain...

06:22.966 --> 06:27.137
...and they said if you write everything down
in a letter and burn it, you'll be healed.

06:27.304 --> 06:28.680
So I started writing...

06:28.847 --> 06:32.059
...and this water
literally started pooling in my eyes.

06:32.226 --> 06:36.313
Has that ever happened to you? Like,
water just oozing out of my eyeballs...

06:36.480 --> 06:39.733
...like I'm some alien creature
excreting fluids.

06:40.150 --> 06:42.194
- You mean you cried?
- Yes.

06:42.903 --> 06:44.988
And after that was done,
I burned the letter.

06:45.155 --> 06:46.657
The feelings, they're still there.

06:49.326 --> 06:53.163
So I really feel strongly
that Jo needs to know how sorry I am...

06:53.330 --> 06:54.873
...for destroying our family.

06:55.499 --> 06:58.669
But let's face it, guys, all right?
I mean, Elena, you of all people...

06:58.836 --> 07:01.672
...should be willing to look past
the things I've done to see...

07:01.839 --> 07:03.674
...that there's good somewhere in me.

07:04.842 --> 07:06.427
- You did it with Damon.
- Okay.

07:06.593 --> 07:08.762
- I think we're done here. Come on.
- Actually...

07:09.847 --> 07:12.724
...what if there's something
he can do for us in exchange?

07:13.183 --> 07:16.353
I'm guessing you didn't bring me out here
to watch you perv out on some co-ed.

07:16.520 --> 07:18.772
It's not just some co-ed.

07:18.939 --> 07:20.941
Meet the real Sarah Salvatore.

07:21.108 --> 07:25.195
The hothouse flower Stefan's been
keeping secret all these years.

07:25.362 --> 07:27.197
Why do you even care?

07:27.739 --> 07:29.783
Because Damon thinks he killed Sarah.

07:29.950 --> 07:33.620
Instead of absolving him, Stefan's using
Damon's guilt to keep him in check.

07:33.787 --> 07:35.789
Not very brotherly now, is it?

07:35.956 --> 07:39.209
So I help you destroy
some innocent girl or what?

07:39.376 --> 07:41.628
You're gonna kill me?
Then go ahead and kill me.

07:41.795 --> 07:44.006
I don't wanna kill you,
just do a few simple tasks.

07:44.173 --> 07:47.301
Screw you, I'm not gonna be your bitch
for the rest of my life.

07:48.760 --> 07:50.012
I don't wanna kill you...

07:50.179 --> 07:51.221
...but I will kill you.

07:51.763 --> 07:53.474
Oh. Look at that.

07:53.640 --> 07:54.850
Very brave.

07:55.017 --> 07:56.894
I admire your tolerance for pain.

07:57.060 --> 07:58.395
Does that run in your family?

07:58.562 --> 08:01.398
Just wondering if your mother,
if she has your pain threshold.

08:03.525 --> 08:07.571
Took a drive down to South Carolina
to take a peek at Mama Donovan.

08:07.738 --> 08:09.823
Quite a dish, that one.

08:11.492 --> 08:12.993
[MATT GASPS]

08:14.203 --> 08:15.245
Good.

08:15.787 --> 08:19.291
Now that that's settled, it's time for you
to get to know Sarah Salvatore.

08:23.253 --> 08:24.880
KAI:
Sad attempt at iron welding.

08:25.047 --> 08:27.090
ELENA:
I tried to fix it.

08:28.342 --> 08:30.010
I can't bring Bonnie back with this.

08:31.261 --> 08:34.389
I thought you are the all-powerful leader
of the Gemini Coven now.

08:34.556 --> 08:35.599
I destroyed this.

08:35.765 --> 08:37.351
So that it couldn't be used again.

08:37.518 --> 08:40.145
Can we use that hunk of junk
to send a message, at least?

08:41.104 --> 08:42.563
It is her birthday.

08:43.023 --> 08:45.067
- It is?
- Yeah.

08:45.234 --> 08:47.569
It's really sad, I mean, little Bon-bon...

08:47.736 --> 08:50.906
...she'll be getting all dressed up
for a party no one's gonna show up to.

08:51.073 --> 08:53.283
I wonder if she even knows...

08:53.450 --> 08:58.413
...that it is her birthday, or do all the
days just blend into one vast sea of misery?

09:00.082 --> 09:01.250
I wonder.

09:05.379 --> 09:07.881
One of the crown wheels survived,
that's a positive.

09:08.757 --> 09:10.050
Plus, I am...

09:10.217 --> 09:11.426
...mega powerful.

09:11.760 --> 09:13.303
Yeah.

09:14.263 --> 09:15.430
What do you wanna say?

09:16.306 --> 09:19.935
Well, Bonnie needs magic to get out, we
just need to tell her where to find some.

09:23.230 --> 09:25.107
[DOOR OPENS]

09:26.233 --> 09:27.776
[CLOSES]

09:31.822 --> 09:34.533
I was gonna wear this
for the merge ceremony.

09:37.411 --> 09:39.246
It's the dress I would have died in.

09:44.209 --> 09:45.836
How could Luke do this?

09:46.753 --> 09:49.131
He didn't do this to you.

09:49.756 --> 09:51.174
Kai did...

09:51.341 --> 09:55.012
...and he's going to finish what he started
by killing you and every other Gemini.

09:55.971 --> 09:59.766
Grab what you need, and let's get out of
here, or Luke will have died for nothing.

10:00.225 --> 10:02.436
Just haul ass out of here like my dad?

10:03.520 --> 10:07.107
Live out the rest of my life wondering,
is today the day that Kai finds me?

10:07.274 --> 10:09.443
I should had just done the stupid merge.

10:11.028 --> 10:13.447
At least, then, Luke and I
would still be together.

10:14.990 --> 10:18.368
All our lives, we've never been apart.

10:19.786 --> 10:21.955
I don't know how to do this.

10:22.122 --> 10:24.249
I'm so sorry, Liv.

10:25.083 --> 10:27.377
I can't run, Tyler.

10:28.503 --> 10:31.423
Kai took my entire life.

10:33.467 --> 10:34.926
There's nowhere for me to go.

10:36.053 --> 10:39.097
Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, look at me, look at me.

10:41.475 --> 10:43.727
Whatever you want to do...

10:44.728 --> 10:46.480
...I will help you get through it.

10:47.397 --> 10:49.191
Fine.

10:51.151 --> 10:53.320
Then I wanna kill Kai.

10:56.782 --> 10:58.867
ELENA: Okay, so we know
that Jo stored her magic...

10:59.034 --> 11:00.410
...in a hunting knife.

11:00.577 --> 11:02.996
Bonnie sent hers over with Miss Cuddles.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.666
What receptacle of magic
am I not thinking of?

11:05.832 --> 11:06.917
Let me give you a hint.

11:07.084 --> 11:08.335
Scorned lover.

11:08.669 --> 11:10.170
- Katherine.
- Older.

11:10.337 --> 11:11.421
- Silas.
- Hotter.

11:11.588 --> 11:12.881
I don't know, Silas was hot.

11:13.048 --> 11:14.925
- Ugh.
- Qetsiyah.

11:15.801 --> 11:18.387
Her blood is on Silas's headstone.
It's filled with magic.

11:18.553 --> 11:21.306
Yup, so in Bonnie-land, that means...

11:21.473 --> 11:25.143
...on an island off Nova Scotia, there's
a magical battery waiting to be tapped.

11:25.310 --> 11:27.396
We just need to remind Bonnie of that.

11:27.562 --> 11:29.231
And what reminded you?

11:29.398 --> 11:31.900
I was just gonna plan a trip there,
change of scenery.

11:32.067 --> 11:34.277
Only so much you can take
of Mystic Falls on repeat.

11:34.444 --> 11:36.780
Oh, thank God. Heh.

11:36.947 --> 11:38.156
You two, together...

11:38.615 --> 11:40.742
...is still totally revolting to me.

11:40.909 --> 11:42.786
Finally, a familiar feeling.

11:42.953 --> 11:44.955
Luke didn't take me over completely.

11:45.747 --> 11:47.290
What the hell is he doing here?

11:48.625 --> 11:50.001
Hi.

11:59.928 --> 12:03.056
If you're gonna creepily stalk me,
you could have at least brought a shovel.

12:03.223 --> 12:05.559
Nah. I'm not big on digging.

12:06.518 --> 12:07.602
Calluses.

12:07.769 --> 12:09.271
You bury corpses all the time.

12:09.438 --> 12:10.772
Yeah, but I don't dig them up.

12:13.316 --> 12:16.027
So do you really think
that finding a teddy bear...

12:16.194 --> 12:18.321
...will make everything right
in the world?

12:18.488 --> 12:19.781
You know what, you are right.

12:19.948 --> 12:21.408
This is such a waste of time.

12:21.575 --> 12:25.495
I should be at the dive bar picking a fight
with a stranger in order to feel pain.

12:25.662 --> 12:27.164
- Ooh.
- Look...

12:27.330 --> 12:29.666
...if you think I'm insane,
I get it, I probably am...

12:29.833 --> 12:31.668
...but nobody is forcing you to be here.

12:31.835 --> 12:32.961
I should probably stay.

12:33.378 --> 12:34.463
Keep an eye on you.

12:34.629 --> 12:36.298
You know, in case you have...

12:36.465 --> 12:37.674
...a psychotic breakdown.

12:41.595 --> 12:43.513
People don't just change like that.

12:43.680 --> 12:46.516
People usually don't merge
with their siblings either.

12:47.058 --> 12:50.270
For the record, I would had been fine
with any of Luke's qualities...

12:50.437 --> 12:52.022
...the hair, the whole gay thing.

12:52.189 --> 12:53.690
You know, maybe not the height.

12:54.232 --> 12:55.817
You seriously buy this?

12:55.984 --> 12:57.694
I'm not saying that we have to like him.

12:57.861 --> 13:00.322
If there's a way for us to tell Bonnie
how to get out...

13:00.489 --> 13:04.159
We should trust the guy
that changed personalities overnight?

13:04.326 --> 13:07.704
Think of it like Elena in reverse.

13:10.123 --> 13:11.625
I know, she was human, pure...

13:11.792 --> 13:15.295
...dating the good Salvatore,
then she became an undead blood-vacuum...

13:15.462 --> 13:17.464
...stopped caring about right and wrong...

13:17.631 --> 13:19.216
...started dating the bad one.

13:19.382 --> 13:20.717
That's not how it happened.

13:20.884 --> 13:23.220
Mm. I'm sure I missed a detail or two.

13:23.386 --> 13:25.931
I'm just paraphrasing what Damon told me
in the prison world.

13:26.097 --> 13:28.809
Speaking of, there's a witch over there
we'd like to save.

13:28.975 --> 13:31.061
So why don't you get
your Gemini jumper cables...

13:31.228 --> 13:33.730
- ...and fix that thing?
- Okay.

13:34.231 --> 13:35.273
[CHANTING IN LATIN]

13:35.440 --> 13:37.484
What are you doing? Liv?

13:38.235 --> 13:40.403
Come on, talk to me.
What are you doing?

13:40.570 --> 13:43.573
When Luke and I were kids,
we used to play hide and seek...

13:43.740 --> 13:47.118
...we found a way to cheat by using a spell
to see through each other's eyes.

13:50.997 --> 13:52.999
[RESUMES CHANTING]

13:55.252 --> 13:56.753
DAMON:
Come on, Kai.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.755
You done yet?

14:02.634 --> 14:04.636
The bastard's at the Salvatore house.

14:04.803 --> 14:06.805
- Why the hell would he be there?
- I have no idea.

14:07.305 --> 14:09.391
Damon would find a reason
to work with him.

14:10.016 --> 14:12.936
Look, Liv. I know how pissed
you are right now, I get that...

14:13.103 --> 14:14.437
...probably more than anybody...

14:14.604 --> 14:17.357
But what? I'm supposed to live with it,
get through it?

14:17.524 --> 14:20.402
Something tells me you didn't punch a wall
after your mom died.

14:20.569 --> 14:23.405
Liv, stop. Like it or
not, Kai is your leader.

14:23.572 --> 14:27.450
You kill him, your entire coven dies,
you, your dad, Jo.

14:28.785 --> 14:31.454
- You.
- We're dead anyway.

14:32.038 --> 14:33.874
He'll kill his way through the coven...

14:34.040 --> 14:37.460
...our friends, the guy at the drive-thru
who screws up his order.

14:38.795 --> 14:40.630
At least this way, I can take him with me.

14:41.756 --> 14:45.010
I told you if anybody tried to hurt you,
they'd have to get through me first.

14:45.176 --> 14:47.804
Well, guess what, that includes you.

14:58.189 --> 15:00.150
[CHANTING SOFTLY]

15:06.031 --> 15:07.824
I'm sorry, Tyler.

15:33.099 --> 15:34.476
[SIGHS]

15:39.856 --> 15:41.441
Heh. I got it.

15:41.608 --> 15:44.319
I'm guessing you're not here
on a basketball scholarship.

15:44.861 --> 15:46.947
That's not a regulation trash can.

15:48.031 --> 15:49.074
Hey.

15:49.240 --> 15:52.202
I saw your camera.
Thinking about buying one. Do you like it?

15:52.369 --> 15:53.703
It gets the job done.

15:53.870 --> 15:55.705
What kind of photography are you into?

15:56.289 --> 15:57.540
A little bit of everything.

15:58.375 --> 16:02.379
Okay, well, it has good color reproduction,
nice tonal range.

16:02.545 --> 16:06.216
You wanna shoot raw, if you don't want
the highlights to get clipped, and...

16:07.509 --> 16:09.719
You have no idea
what I'm talking about, do you?

16:09.886 --> 16:12.555
No. No, I don't, sorry.

16:12.722 --> 16:14.140
Don't feel bad, you went for it.

16:14.307 --> 16:17.394
Not your fault you led with the second
most common pickup line guys use...

16:17.560 --> 16:19.229
...when they see a girl with a camera.

16:19.396 --> 16:22.565
- What's the first?
- They offer to pose for some tasteful nudes.

16:22.732 --> 16:24.567
[BOTH LAUGH]

16:24.734 --> 16:26.569
Look, I'm really flattered...

16:26.903 --> 16:28.905
...and I'm sure you're a nice guy, but...

16:29.072 --> 16:31.366
No, it's okay, I get it.

16:33.451 --> 16:36.496
- Good luck with your photography.
- Thanks.

16:41.418 --> 16:43.753
You truly have an epic lack of game.

16:43.920 --> 16:45.296
- I tried, okay.
- Really?

16:45.463 --> 16:47.424
Grunting at her would've been
more effective.

16:48.299 --> 16:49.634
I gotta get you back on track.

16:50.010 --> 16:53.263
Right, give me your jacket,
your wallet and your cell phone.

16:54.931 --> 16:56.766
So I can't send us back physically...

16:56.933 --> 16:58.768
...but I can probably
send a part of us back.

16:58.935 --> 17:01.271
- Probably?
- You remember the movie <i>Ghost?</i>

17:01.438 --> 17:04.691
Okay, Bonnie is gonna be Demi Moore
because she's the alive one...

17:04.858 --> 17:08.194
...and we'll all be a
collective Patrick Swayze.

17:08.528 --> 17:11.031
The ghost. By the way,
how much does that suck?

17:11.614 --> 17:14.951
- About Patrick Swayze.
- Will she be able to see us or not, Kai?

17:15.535 --> 17:17.162
I don't know, I've never done this.

17:18.288 --> 17:20.457
So let's all just take
a deep breath, right?

17:21.415 --> 17:22.459
Close our eyes.

17:23.417 --> 17:25.127
And?

17:25.670 --> 17:27.464
[KAI CHANTING IN LATIN]

17:43.313 --> 17:45.148
What happened to the pool table?

17:47.192 --> 17:48.443
Oh, my God.

17:52.947 --> 17:55.075
Bonnie? Bonnie!

17:57.660 --> 17:58.703
She can't hear me.

18:01.331 --> 18:03.333
We can't touch anything, either.

18:03.708 --> 18:05.001
Nice spell, Kai.

18:07.837 --> 18:11.049
<i>This place is my own personal hell.</i>

18:11.216 --> 18:13.009
- Drama queen.
- Hey.

18:14.010 --> 18:17.305
<i>Reporting to you live from retro world,
I'm Bonnie Bennett...</i>

18:17.472 --> 18:21.851
<i>...joining us today in the studio
is special guest Damon Salvatore.</i>

18:28.191 --> 18:30.276
- No.
- What?

18:30.568 --> 18:32.904
That bottle of bourbon is the oldest one
in the house.

18:33.905 --> 18:38.368
We made a pact, if we couldn't take being
trapped here alone for one more day, we'd...

18:38.868 --> 18:40.537
We'd kill that entire bottle.

18:44.624 --> 18:46.042
And then we'd kill ourselves.

18:51.756 --> 18:53.258
[GASPS]

18:57.262 --> 18:58.930
What happened? Why are we back here?

19:00.140 --> 19:02.559
KAI: I don't know,
spell must require too much magic.

19:02.725 --> 19:03.768
I lost my connection.

19:03.935 --> 19:05.895
- Then reconnect.
- It's not that easy.

19:06.062 --> 19:09.899
- You see this blood? That's not a good sign.
- Bonnie is going to kill herself.

19:10.066 --> 19:11.901
Can she do that? Can she die there?

19:12.068 --> 19:14.904
I couldn't. Of course, it was
my own personal solitary confinement.

19:15.071 --> 19:17.365
Didn't want me to end my sentence
by killing myself.

19:17.532 --> 19:19.409
Ooh. I tried every method in the book.

19:19.576 --> 19:23.454
I drove down to D.C. because there was
this museum that has an actual guillotine.

19:23.621 --> 19:27.041
We get it, for whoever is not lucky enough
to be you, dead means dead.

19:27.208 --> 19:30.420
We have to stop her, we have to give
her hope. Send her a message somehow.

19:30.920 --> 19:33.423
- How? She couldn't hear us.
- Message is already there.

19:33.590 --> 19:37.427
In the atlas. I scribbled some notes
on Nova Scotia, have to get her to see it.

19:37.594 --> 19:40.263
How do we open an atlas
if we can't touch anything?

19:40.722 --> 19:43.558
We need to get Kai to crank up
his witchy-woo, don't we?

19:43.725 --> 19:45.393
So we can make physical contact.

19:45.768 --> 19:49.272
All while sending the three of you back
over there? Sure, yeah.

19:49.439 --> 19:51.858
Why don't I reanimate your parents
for a tea party?

19:52.734 --> 19:53.776
Sorry.

19:55.236 --> 19:56.279
Insensitive.

19:56.446 --> 19:58.198
What if you just send me back?

19:58.364 --> 20:00.283
- What? No.
KAI: That might work.

20:00.450 --> 20:02.452
I focus all of my magic on one person.

20:03.453 --> 20:06.456
It might be enough of a boost
that he could physically interact.

20:07.040 --> 20:08.583
If I can hold the spell.

20:09.125 --> 20:10.960
And if you cannot?

20:11.878 --> 20:14.047
The magic overwhelms me...

20:14.631 --> 20:17.759
...and I can't pull Jeremy out,
he'll be stuck there for eternity.

20:18.801 --> 20:20.720
- Jer...
- Don't. Don't say anything.

20:20.887 --> 20:24.182
If I can get through to her,
we save Bonnie's life, if not...

20:25.642 --> 20:27.560
...at least I'll be with her
when she dies.

20:30.605 --> 20:31.981
[GRUNTS]

20:32.357 --> 20:33.566
[EXHALES]

20:33.733 --> 20:34.901
Hey, is that an M&M?

20:35.401 --> 20:36.986
- Where?
- Right there.

20:37.153 --> 20:40.990
Little to the left. Little to the left.
Right there. Ri... Wha... Whoa. Oh.

20:41.157 --> 20:43.409
Sorry, it was just a leaf.

20:45.411 --> 20:46.621
Is this funny to you?

20:46.788 --> 20:48.748
Well, we are in the middle of the woods...

20:48.915 --> 20:53.878
...searching for a teddy bear buried in a
shallow grave by a 9-year-old version of you.

20:54.045 --> 20:56.881
I can't even say it with a straight face.
So, yeah, that is funny.

20:57.048 --> 20:59.342
- You're drunk. Give me that.
- No, no, no.

20:59.509 --> 21:01.344
You have more ground to cover.

21:01.844 --> 21:03.513
You're a jerk.

21:03.680 --> 21:05.014
- Jerk, huh?
- Yeah.

21:05.181 --> 21:07.517
- Now you sound angry.
- I'm not...

21:07.684 --> 21:09.769
...angry, okay? I'm just annoyed.

21:09.936 --> 21:12.355
I'm going through
an emotional situation right now...

21:12.522 --> 21:14.857
...and you're just sitting
there, mocking me.

21:15.316 --> 21:17.568
- Definitely angry.
- I'm not angry.

21:17.735 --> 21:19.362
- Okay?
- Well, you should be.

21:19.529 --> 21:22.198
Your mom is dying.
Best friend's stuck in some netherworld...

21:22.365 --> 21:24.867
...and you're here trying to find
a stuffed animal?

21:25.034 --> 21:26.661
Shut up!

21:28.246 --> 21:30.164
- That make you feel better?
- No.

21:30.331 --> 21:31.666
- Try again.
- Screw you!

21:33.626 --> 21:35.044
That's good. Get it out.

21:36.629 --> 21:37.797
[GRUNTS]

21:44.554 --> 21:46.389
[BOTH GRUNTING]

21:47.765 --> 21:49.684
I cannot believe you just did that.

21:49.851 --> 21:52.145
Well, you started it.

21:55.189 --> 21:57.400
It felt good though, didn't it?

21:59.152 --> 22:00.737
Maybe a little.

22:00.903 --> 22:02.572
[BOTH LAUGH]

22:05.241 --> 22:07.327
[CHANTING]

22:08.161 --> 22:10.580
I didn't know
you and Bonnie had a death pact.

22:11.372 --> 22:12.540
DAMON:
It was my idea.

22:12.707 --> 22:15.918
I thought of it after we watched
<i>The Bodyguard</i> for the billionth time.

22:16.669 --> 22:18.254
[CONTINUES CHANTING]

22:18.421 --> 22:20.840
I never thought she'd go through with it.

22:21.841 --> 22:23.426
I can't watch this.

22:38.441 --> 22:39.650
Hey.

22:39.817 --> 22:42.779
- Ansel Adams.
- I have no idea who that is.

22:43.446 --> 22:46.282
- Where are you trying to go?
- Virginia.

22:46.449 --> 22:48.368
- Mystic Falls.
- Virginia?

22:49.202 --> 22:51.454
This is a campus bus. It
has, like, five stops.

22:53.331 --> 22:55.583
- Farthest you'll get is Lenox Hospital.
- Great.

22:55.750 --> 22:58.628
My buddy bailed on me, and my phone
and jacket are in his car.

23:00.713 --> 23:02.965
This is why I don't visit animal shelters.

23:03.132 --> 23:05.885
Come on. I'll show you
where you can catch a real bus.

23:06.052 --> 23:07.929
Oh, that'd be great. I'm...

23:08.096 --> 23:10.807
- ...freezing out here.
- There's a cafe on the way.

23:10.973 --> 23:13.142
We'll get a coffee, and you can warm up.

23:13.643 --> 23:15.520
Too bad my wallet's in my jacket.

23:15.686 --> 23:17.897
How were you planning
on paying for the bus?

23:18.356 --> 23:19.440
Charm?

23:20.316 --> 23:23.778
Yeah, well, in that case, I'll buy you
a bus ticket to go with that coffee.

23:23.945 --> 23:24.987
Thank you.

23:25.780 --> 23:26.989
Come on.

23:34.163 --> 23:35.498
Our suicide bourbon.

23:36.499 --> 23:39.836
Bonnie and I made a pact we'd drink
this together, that's what I'll do.

23:44.424 --> 23:45.675
Mmm.

23:48.302 --> 23:50.179
To you, Bonnie.

23:54.642 --> 23:55.685
Oh.

24:00.022 --> 24:02.692
So was Kai right about me?

24:03.192 --> 24:06.487
By turning into a vampire,
I completely changed?

24:06.654 --> 24:08.197
Kai is a psychopath.

24:08.364 --> 24:09.991
Don't let him get in your head.

24:10.533 --> 24:12.285
I'm not.

24:12.618 --> 24:16.873
But do you ever think about it, like, if I
would still be with you if I was human?

24:18.416 --> 24:20.209
Okay, we're doing this.

24:21.627 --> 24:24.005
It's just a question, Damon.

24:27.008 --> 24:28.551
- No.
- No, what?

24:28.718 --> 24:31.804
No, I don't think we'd be together
if you were still human.

24:32.305 --> 24:34.557
You had a choice. You chose Stefan.

24:34.724 --> 24:37.518
Human you was on your way home to him.

24:37.685 --> 24:39.145
Car went off the bridge.

24:40.521 --> 24:43.566
You turned, and suddenly
I was back in the picture.

24:48.696 --> 24:50.740
I'm gonna go check on Jer.

24:54.327 --> 24:55.495
[GRUNTS]

24:56.829 --> 24:58.539
What's going on?

24:59.832 --> 25:01.792
JEREMY:
Okay, 1994, let's do this.

25:01.959 --> 25:04.212
KAI:
Where's the stupid map?

25:09.425 --> 25:11.594
- It's working.
- Hurry up and find Nova Scotia.

25:13.095 --> 25:14.347
Nova Scotia, got it.

25:15.264 --> 25:17.099
What?

25:18.100 --> 25:19.268
Kai, do something.

25:22.188 --> 25:23.231
Kai?

25:29.779 --> 25:31.489
No, what are you doing?

25:39.872 --> 25:40.998
[CHUCKLES]

25:42.792 --> 25:44.168
Dang, sis.

25:44.335 --> 25:46.128
- That was harsh.
- Shut up.

25:48.256 --> 25:49.799
[YELLING]

25:52.552 --> 25:54.136
[CHANTS]

25:54.762 --> 25:56.305
[YELPS]

25:56.472 --> 25:58.140
[CHUCKLES]

26:00.685 --> 26:03.813
It's all coming back to me, Livie-poo.

26:05.314 --> 26:07.650
- You know the charge...
- Stop it, Kai.

26:07.817 --> 26:10.319
- ...that races through your bones...
- Stop it.

26:10.486 --> 26:12.822
...at the prospect
of watching someone burn to death.

26:15.157 --> 26:16.909
I really miss that feeling.

26:17.410 --> 26:19.203
[CHUCKLES]

26:22.999 --> 26:24.208
Just kill me, Kai.

26:25.376 --> 26:27.920
You already killed my best friend.

26:29.338 --> 26:30.923
So just do it.

26:31.841 --> 26:33.384
Get it over with.

26:36.429 --> 26:38.180
Why can't I do this?

26:40.850 --> 26:42.602
[SOBS]

26:46.772 --> 26:48.232
I don't care about you.

26:52.903 --> 26:54.822
Why can't I kill her? Come on.

26:54.989 --> 26:56.240
Kai, do it.

26:56.407 --> 26:57.950
Do it.

26:58.451 --> 26:59.994
Come on!

27:00.161 --> 27:01.370
Kill her!

27:12.298 --> 27:13.716
[YELPS]

27:17.553 --> 27:19.055
What the hell's happening?

27:19.221 --> 27:20.890
[LIV AND KAI GRUNTING]

27:22.058 --> 27:23.726
Liv's trying to kill Kai.

27:23.893 --> 27:24.935
Jeremy.

27:26.604 --> 27:28.439
Jeremy.

27:31.901 --> 27:34.612
Send me back. Please.

27:34.779 --> 27:36.614
Jeremy, look at me.

27:36.781 --> 27:39.992
- I'm half dead.
- I need to stop Bonnie.

27:41.702 --> 27:42.912
Okay.

27:43.079 --> 27:44.246
Okay.

27:44.497 --> 27:46.415
[CHANTING IN LATIN]

28:01.013 --> 28:03.432
Cheers to making it this far.

28:23.119 --> 28:24.704
Okay.

28:24.870 --> 28:27.748
I think it's time I cut myself off.

28:42.388 --> 28:43.806
[YELLS]

28:52.565 --> 28:53.983
Stay here.

28:54.150 --> 28:57.987
Well, I think I got all the catharsis
out of this that I'm gonna get.

28:58.654 --> 29:01.323
- Let's go home.
- All right.

29:03.826 --> 29:05.661
Wait a minute.

29:06.162 --> 29:07.371
- What is that?
- Shut up.

29:07.538 --> 29:09.540
No, no, no. I'm serious.

29:09.707 --> 29:11.584
Is that an ear?

29:12.042 --> 29:13.794
Oh, my God.

29:22.720 --> 29:24.346
Cuddles.

29:24.513 --> 29:26.599
I'm sure we can clean her up.

29:26.766 --> 29:28.058
Make her as good as new.

29:28.225 --> 29:30.853
Yeah, the...

29:37.401 --> 29:39.195
[BOTH LAUGH]

29:52.708 --> 29:54.126
[SOFTLY]
Hey.

29:59.089 --> 30:00.883
Hey, I'm sorry.

30:11.227 --> 30:13.062
[SOBBING]

30:23.906 --> 30:25.658
Kai!

30:26.158 --> 30:27.618
Get out here!

30:29.578 --> 30:30.913
[GRUNTS]

30:31.080 --> 30:32.414
She's right below us.

30:32.581 --> 30:34.834
LIV:
<i>You can't hide from me.</i>

30:35.918 --> 30:37.586
What are you doing?

30:47.555 --> 30:50.599
I said I was saving this
for something special.

30:52.893 --> 30:54.144
[SHRIEKS]

31:13.873 --> 31:15.332
[ENGINE STARTS]

31:24.550 --> 31:26.010
[COUGHS]

31:31.140 --> 31:33.017
No, come on.

31:33.183 --> 31:36.312
You don't wanna do this.
Just turn off the car, Bonnie.

31:37.479 --> 31:38.647
You can't die.

31:38.814 --> 31:41.358
It's probably a waste of time
even recording anything.

31:41.525 --> 31:43.903
But, Damon, Elena...

31:44.528 --> 31:45.654
...or whoever...

31:45.821 --> 31:49.783
...if you find this and you figured out
how to work this stupid thing...

31:50.409 --> 31:52.828
...please tell everyone that I'm sorry.

31:53.704 --> 31:55.039
Bonnie.

31:55.205 --> 31:56.999
Tell them that I tried.

31:57.166 --> 31:59.793
I really tried to make it work.

32:01.003 --> 32:02.379
Um...

32:03.047 --> 32:04.798
You know, I just miss it too much.

32:06.675 --> 32:09.511
I miss saying hi to strangers.

32:11.430 --> 32:13.724
Ordering dinner...

32:13.891 --> 32:15.517
...in a restaurant.

32:16.644 --> 32:20.356
Laughing with my friends.

32:22.983 --> 32:24.401
But, um...

32:24.568 --> 32:27.237
...spending every day here alone...

32:27.571 --> 32:30.074
...with no one to talk to...

32:30.532 --> 32:32.660
...going weeks without speaking...

32:33.535 --> 32:37.831
...it's just the loneliness.
It's, uh... I can't take it.

32:44.046 --> 32:46.840
And I only know one way to turn it off.

32:49.051 --> 32:50.511
I'm sorry.

32:54.390 --> 32:55.599
Jeremy.

32:57.851 --> 32:59.103
I...

32:59.269 --> 33:02.022
I hope you're living your life...

33:02.398 --> 33:04.066
...with no regrets.

33:05.192 --> 33:07.861
Hope you fight for the life you want.

33:09.071 --> 33:11.907
And don't ever give up on yourself.

33:12.741 --> 33:14.785
And stay strong.

33:18.914 --> 33:21.291
That's what my grams said.

33:22.876 --> 33:24.586
[COUGHING]

33:25.713 --> 33:27.089
Stay...

33:27.798 --> 33:29.550
...strong.

33:35.264 --> 33:36.974
[COUGHING]

33:42.438 --> 33:43.605
Come on, Bonnie. Get up.

33:46.108 --> 33:47.359
Come on.

33:47.526 --> 33:49.069
Gonna stay strong.

33:49.236 --> 33:51.113
I'm not gonna die in this place.

33:51.280 --> 33:53.157
Bonnie, come on. Get up.

33:55.159 --> 33:58.162
Bonnie, get up. Open. Come on.

34:00.789 --> 34:02.624
Come on!

34:07.421 --> 34:08.630
[GASPS]

34:20.309 --> 34:22.811
Oh, Jeremy. Jeremy.

34:22.978 --> 34:24.980
Hey, Jeremy. Wake up.

34:25.147 --> 34:26.982
Kai. Hey. Wake up.

34:27.149 --> 34:28.692
Damn it.

34:36.116 --> 34:39.369
Jeremy, wake up. Jer, wake up.

34:40.621 --> 34:41.955
Jeremy.

34:42.664 --> 34:43.706
I'm okay.

34:48.378 --> 34:51.005
Bonnie, is she...?

34:51.590 --> 34:52.632
I saw her.

34:54.134 --> 34:55.636
She's gonna be okay.

35:13.987 --> 35:16.156
We might be able to salvage a piece.

35:16.323 --> 35:20.160
I don't think Bonnie would want us
to let cake go to waste.

35:27.042 --> 35:29.503
You know, I get it.
I get what she was going through.

35:30.546 --> 35:32.047
Why she would want to end it.

35:33.048 --> 35:35.175
Feeling trapped and alone.

35:36.218 --> 35:39.429
Every day is the same.
Disappointment, misery. You...

35:40.305 --> 35:42.933
...go to sleep and wake up
and do it all over again.

35:45.185 --> 35:47.437
But she's not the only one that's trapped.

35:49.690 --> 35:51.775
Jeremy, I know
what you've been going through.

35:51.942 --> 35:54.570
- Don't tell me I gotta be strong.
- Actually...

35:55.571 --> 35:58.198
...I was gonna say it's okay to move on.

35:59.366 --> 36:02.244
Bonnie decided to save herself.

36:02.411 --> 36:04.163
And from what you told me...

36:04.329 --> 36:06.540
...I think she wants you to do the same.

36:09.084 --> 36:12.921
Go to art school. We'll all help you.
Just...

36:13.380 --> 36:15.966
Just find the life that you want.

36:16.550 --> 36:18.051
And be happy.

36:18.719 --> 36:20.387
What about you?

36:21.930 --> 36:22.973
I'll be fine.

36:24.683 --> 36:25.767
I promise.

36:27.060 --> 36:28.770
Just get out of here.

36:31.732 --> 36:33.734
And don't look back.

36:46.496 --> 36:47.915
How did I get back here?

36:50.792 --> 36:53.337
Well, first, I woke up on the floor.

36:54.171 --> 36:56.632
I guess a pillow would have been
too much to ask for.

36:57.007 --> 37:00.636
And when I figured out where you've gone,
I raced over to the Salvatore house.

37:00.802 --> 37:02.804
Only to find you unconscious.

37:04.181 --> 37:06.391
I convinced Elena
to give you some of her blood.

37:10.020 --> 37:11.605
And now that I see you're okay...

37:13.398 --> 37:15.150
...I never wanna see you again.

37:15.651 --> 37:17.361
- Tyler, wait.
- You lied to me.

37:17.527 --> 37:20.030
- No, I never wanted to hurt you.
- You lied to me.

37:20.197 --> 37:22.824
- Please, just calm down, okay?
- I'm not gonna calm down.

37:22.991 --> 37:25.202
I would have done anything for you.

37:25.827 --> 37:27.704
And you chose death over me.

37:33.210 --> 37:34.628
[DOOR CLOSES]

37:40.968 --> 37:42.052
[SIGHS]

37:42.219 --> 37:44.930
So how was your little coffee date?

37:45.806 --> 37:48.141
Heh. You fancy her, don't you?

37:48.308 --> 37:49.851
What was the point of this?

37:50.018 --> 37:51.478
You were a test.

37:51.645 --> 37:55.315
I wanted to see what kind of person
the last remaining Salvatore really is.

37:55.482 --> 37:56.900
What kind of person she is?

37:57.067 --> 37:59.528
She spurned your comically-inept attempts
to charm her...

37:59.695 --> 38:02.489
...and yet proved to be a good Samaritan
when you needed assistance.

38:03.031 --> 38:07.828
On a scale of one to 10,
I'd say her purity ranks about 9.5.

38:09.371 --> 38:12.165
- When I'm through with her, she'll be a one.
- So, what?

38:12.332 --> 38:16.211
- You're gonna compel her to be bad?
- I'm not gonna compel her.

38:16.378 --> 38:19.798
I want Sarah to know that everything
she did was of her own free will.

38:20.465 --> 38:21.717
What are you talking about?

38:23.760 --> 38:26.013
I'm going to insinuate
myself into her life.

38:26.596 --> 38:29.850
Make her do things
she had never dreamed of doing...

38:30.017 --> 38:32.561
...until she begs me to make her a vampire.

38:33.186 --> 38:34.396
[CHUCKLES]

38:36.064 --> 38:38.317
Stefan thought he could protect her.

38:39.192 --> 38:41.069
I'm gonna show him how wrong he is.

38:47.701 --> 38:50.370
So Jer's applying to art school. Hm.

38:51.413 --> 38:55.459
Might want to compel him a decent
portfolio, because he ain't that great.

38:55.625 --> 38:56.877
Don't be mean.

38:57.044 --> 39:00.547
- Heh.
- He needs to move on with his life and...

39:01.631 --> 39:02.883
...so do I.

39:03.258 --> 39:05.427
I'm not sure I'm a fan of that transition.

39:06.762 --> 39:08.889
Look, I've...

39:09.848 --> 39:12.851
...made some huge mistakes in my life.

39:13.977 --> 39:15.562
Being with you wasn't one of them.

39:16.730 --> 39:20.609
And, yes, I had Alaric compel away
my love for you.

39:20.942 --> 39:23.653
And, yes, I did love Stefan once.

39:24.529 --> 39:26.073
The night I died...

39:26.740 --> 39:29.618
...Matt was driving me back to him.

39:30.118 --> 39:32.996
And yet, I found my way back to you.

39:34.039 --> 39:38.418
Damon, I somehow always find my way
back to you.

39:39.753 --> 39:44.758
It doesn't matter if I have memories or not.
It doesn't matter if I'm a vampire or not.

39:47.761 --> 39:50.597
You're just saying that because
you can't change what you are.

39:50.764 --> 39:53.767
No, Damon. I don't care what human me
would have done.

39:53.934 --> 39:55.644
Because she's not here, I am.

39:58.063 --> 40:00.399
And if the past is a place...

40:00.565 --> 40:03.193
...without you and me together...

40:04.194 --> 40:06.446
...then let's stop living in it.

40:07.197 --> 40:08.281
Yeah.

41:21.897 --> 41:23.940
Nova Scotia?

41:24.107 --> 41:27.486
Damon, you're a genius.

41:43.877 --> 41:45.295
[ENGINE STARTS]

42:21.164 --> 42:23.166
[English - US - SDH]
